        "As touched on in https://github.com/rethinkdb/rethinkdb/issues/281#issuecomment-39374820 and #4316, defining a simpler stable abstraction interface for `Connection` when called by a query's `.run()` that wouldn't be reliant on digging far into the internals of the AST for its interface would allow for things like:\n- drop in connections / cross-pollination with alternative drivers/implementations like `reqlite`\n- alternative connection modules using pools (#281) and/or pre-connection query buffering (#4315)\n  - these could be betas/polyfills for prospective inclusion into the main upstream driver\n"
